author: CNN
description: About 40 people were killed and around 115 others injured in a fire at a New Year’s party in a Swiss ski resort bar, according to police. It will take time to identify all the victims and the cause of the deadly fire, officials said.
title: Deadly fire at Swiss bar during New Year’s party

author: CNN
description: Local residents describe people screaming, struggling to escape, and calling for help after a fire broke out during a New Year’s party at the Le Constellation. Police say dozens of people are presumed dead and around 100 others were injured in the blaze in Crans-Montana, as authorities investigate the cause and keep the area closed to the public.
title: Eyewitnesses describes chaos after deadly Swiss resort fire

About 100 people were inside the venue at a Swiss ski resort when a deadly fire broke out, according to Gaetan Lathion, spokesperson for police in the canton of Valais. 

The fire began at Crans-Montana, one of Switzerland’s most exclusive locales, at around 1:30 a.m. on January 1.

description: Flames tore through the steeple of Vondelkerk in Amsterdam over New Year’s, forcing evacuations as debris fell onto nearby homes. No casualties have been reported, and the cause is under investigation.
title: Fire breaks out at historic Amsterdam church

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump rang in the New Year with the First Lady at his Mar-a-Lago club in Palm Beach, Florida. Trump auctioned off a portrait of Jesus for nearly $3 million dollars. Trump says half of the money would go to St. Jude’s Children's Hospital and the rest would go to the local sheriff’s department.
title: President Trump rings in the New Year

description: In his New Year’s Eve address, Chinese leader Xi Jinping strikes an upbeat tone, highlighting confidence in China’s economy and technological competitiveness despite ongoing U.S. trade tariffs. Xi also reiterates Beijing’s stance on Taiwan, describing reunification as "unavoidable." CNN’s Steven Jiang and Simone McCarthy report.
title: China strikes upbeat tone for 2026 while holding firm on Taiwan
